Why I rejected Ultimate Sinatra
- Dynamic/preserved nuance vs. consistent loudness and immediacy: Ultimate Sinatra is described as preserving wide dynamic range and being “curated to breathe rather than flatten vocals.” While that is excellent for nuanced, cinematic listening, it runs counter to my explicit preference for consistent loudness and radio‑style immediacy that supports repeat, casual listening. I prefer discs that are uniformly polished and immediately replayable; an album that intentionally preserves wide dynamics will be less consistent in perceived loudness and punch on modern systems.
