In short, the pop/dance‑pop greatest‑hits disc better satisfies my core requirements — radio‑ready production, clear lead vocals, consistent loudness, clean stereo imaging, concise arrangements, singalong hooks and tight sequencing for immediate replayability — while the Sinatra set, despite high‑quality mastering and vocal focus, emphasizes dynamics, nuance and cinematic pacing that conflict with my preference for uniformly polished, immediately replayable pop compilations.

