- Roomy, cinematic mixes vs rhythmic punch: Although Sinatra offers warm analogue remastering, natural vocal presence and LP‑style sequencing (all points I like), the anthology is characterized by roomy, cinematic mixes and spacious orchestral layering. That room‑centric, orchestral presentation runs the risk of sacrificing the immediate, muscular rhythmic punch I prioritize. My dislike of “piano‑first or room‑centric ambience that sacrifices rhythmic punch” makes Sinatra less appealing in this context.
