- Sing‑along and modern immediacy: Prince’s concise, radio‑friendly edits and upfront funk arrangements are more likely to be sing‑along friendly and rhythmically immediate than the cinematic balladry and large‑room sound of the Sinatra anthology.
In sum, the Prince compilation better satisfies my core requirements for upfront-but‑natural vocals, preserved dynamics, percussive rhythmic drive and clear instrument separation, while the Sinatra anthology’s roomy orchestral presentation conflicts with my dislike of room‑centric mixes that blunt rhythmic immediacy.

